# Supabase — public (browser-safe) credentials used by the supplier directory.
# Both must be set for the directory to load suppliers; without them the app
# shows an explicit error/empty state (there is no bundled mock fallback).
# Find these in your Supabase project: Settings → API.
#
# SECURITY: only ever expose the anon/publishable key via NEXT_PUBLIC_*.
# NEVER put the service_role key in a NEXT_PUBLIC_* variable — it bypasses
# Row Level Security and would be shipped to every visitor's browser.
# Make sure Row Level Security (RLS) is enabled on all Supabase tables.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
# Use the publishable key, or the anon key if that's what your deployment
# provides (the Supabase→Vercel integration injects NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY).
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
